  "market_context": "Daily chart showed a retest of a bullish fair value gap (FVG) and sweep of prior day low forming a protected low. Hourly confirmed change in state of delivery (CISD) and order block. Analyst then dropped to 5-minute for precise entries during London and NY sessions.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the previous day low, closed back inside the range, forming a protected low and retesting a daily bullish FVG—establishing strong bullish bias for the session.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, analyst identified a sweep of the previous day low followed by a close back inside the range, forming a protected low and retesting a bullish fair value gap (FVG), establishing bullish bias.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the hourly chart to confirm structure: identified a change in state of delivery (CISD) via closure through down-close candles, forming a bullish order block near 147.400–147.800.",
    "Step 3: Entered first trade on 5-minute after London session sweep and CISD confirmation off the hourly order block, targeting daily highs for 2R and runners to hourly projections.",
    "Step 4: After initial move, price retraced into the hourly order block again; analyst waited for second CISD on 5-minute (closure through down-close candles) and took a second entry with same target structure.",
    "Step 5: Verified time frame alignment: daily bias bullish, hourly structure bullish (CISD + OB), and 5-minute entries aligned—triggering expansion toward daily highs."
  ],
  "outcome": "Two successful long entries taken on 5-minute: first during London session, second after retracement; both reached 2R targets at daily highs, with runners extended to hourly standard deviation projections.",
  "lessons": "Bullish bias is confirmed when daily FVG is retested after a protected low forms; lower timeframe entries require CISD + POI confluence; multiple entries are valid when structure holds and time frames realign after retracement.",
